node.text:
A lil self love mantra 🌹🌛
Repeat after me:

Light of the stars within me,
I'm full of inspiration.
I manifest deep presence,
My life is my creation.

My heart is healed and open,
Love flows through my being.
I'm present in each moment,
I love the dream I'm living.

Abundance is my birthright,
I evolve and grow.
I trust the divine plan
And go with life's flow.

🤍✨

node.text:
Swipe swipe swipe 🌹
The book I am currently creating has been writing itself for the past 10 years. Since last year I knew I wanted to put my journal entries to use. I wanted to present them to the world, in a way that was fun and beautiful and deep.

This is the most vulnerable project I've ever committed myself to, and I feel like it will be the most healing, too. For you and for me. Stay tuned. New book coming in early 2022, a collection of my own journal entries, poems, stories and musings. 🌙✨

node.text:
I dreamt about the Atlantis last night.

From my notes...
"5 August
I have a stressful dream prior to this so when I feel myself drifting off to another dream and I literally set an intention "please please make this one a beautiful one"

I am on the top of a Japanese looking building / temple, on a small island surrounded by the ocean and waves and I think to myself "are you kidding me." (Because whenever I dream of the ocean, scary tidal waves come and I have to run away) Of course massive waves come from all angles but instead of flooding this time, they rise and make a dome over me and the island. The island with me on it is being submerged under water. I am in a small room now and suddenly all the walls become sealed so water doesn't get in. There are small windows and I peak outside and we're going to the bottom of the ocean floor, down, down, down. This takes a while probably lasts for what felt like 10 minutes. 
I feel that we landed on the bottom and movement stops. 
I get out of the room and this is it, Atlantis. I just look around and go for a little walk. The locals are there too. They are half naked and covered in paint like from the movie Atlantis mixed with Avatar. They're friendly. I ask them to teach me their "greeting". One of them interlaces their fingers with mine, looks me in the eyes and says "Bless." I make a mental note in my mind to remember this, I have to remember this moment. 
Not sure where the dream goes after that's all I remember."

Do you think it was just a dream or something more?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by DreamyMoons on August 03, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
I once read that stars burst, so I could exist. 
They gave up its light just for me. 
Which means life comes from death,
What a plot twist!
What a powerful reason to BE.

We are stars in human bodies,
Stardust with eyes and legs.
Laughing and crying, rushing and running,
Remembering our way back.

How can we return to the light that we are?
Perhaps we can search within. 
You don't need a spaceship, or rocket, or plane,
Just close your eyes and breathe in.

And when you breathe out, remember
That you are more than you know.
Remember that place you came from
A billion years ago.

-Annie Tarasova / DreamyMoons 🌙

A new book is in the making ✨

node.text:
Swipe to read the whole poem ✨
This one was inspired by my diary entry from 2015: "I was laying on the grass, staring into a sea of glistening stars. Hypnotised by a bottomless ocean of galaxies, planets and suns, I envisioned myself floating in space, looking back on Earth. Our home. A blue ball spinning in mysterious nothingness. With everyone on it. You, me, our family, our friends, our enemies, people we’ve walked past on the street, people haven’t met yet, people we will never meet. On it are places we’ve been to before, places we are yet to visit, and places we will never visit in this lifetime. 

Earth. This magnificent planet, that was kind enough to let us inhibit it. To let us use her resources. Our mother. The Earth was spinning just like it has been spinning for the past 4.5 billion years. 

A sense of realisation washed over me. Deep from within, I freed myself from what was troubling my mind. I realised that no matter what I worry about at this present moment, the Earth is still spinning. No matter what happens in this lifetime of mine, the Earth will continue spinning. 

I am insignificant. 

No matter how frightening that might sound to you, at that moment, that was the most comforting feeling in the world.

Insignificant, yet a part of something so big that it goes beyond my understanding. A part of you, a part of every tree, every flower, and every living being on Earth. I was immersed in two conflicting feelings, merged into one beautiful experience - unity and separation."

This collection (available in both silver and gold!) was created in a collaboration with the wonderful @krystleknightjewellery and will go LIVE on their website next SUNDAY, 25 JULY! Mark your calendars ✨

Also - make sure to sign up to mine or Krystle Knight Jewellery email list for an early birds access AND a 10% discount when the time comes 😇 (just click website link in bio and a pop up window will come up)

Lastly, I am just so excited to share these creations with you, inspired by the raw moonstone and mama Moon herself 🌝 KKJ have been a dream to work with, and I couldn’t be happier with how the collection turned out. You can now wear my art, how freaking cool! 

Comment which piece you’re loving the most?

node.text:
I have thought and spoken about this dream / memory for years. For so long that I forgot when it actually came to me. I thought may be I had this dream when I was going through my spiritual awakening, or when I started pondering what happens before birth or after death. 

The other day I was looking through my old journals, just for fun. I started journaling at 11 years old (so glad I did - some stuff I wrote back then is hilarious). And there it was. A journal entry from the actual day I had this dream. To my absolute surprise, I was only 13 when it came to me.

Naturally, I had to create a poem about it and illustrate it!

Comments and feedback is much appreciated - I put my heart and soul into my art and Instagram is making it harder and harder and artists to get noticed (as the algorithm now much prefers video posts) thank you so much for your love & support ❤️

node.text:
Soul Whispers card deck stole many hearts since I released it in April ✨🤍 I’m mesmerized by its enchanting gold foil every time I use it! It’s so special to hold my idea in my hands, crafted and designed with so much love and attention to details.

The idea behind this deck is a bit different to your usual oracle / tarot deck, although you can definitely use it the same way. Each card is a message from your higher self - a prompt for thought, a piece of wisdom or even an answer to your question. It’s up to you how to interpret it 🌙

Available at www.dreamymoons.com.au 🤍
